article.headline: Delaware 81, George Mason 78 (OT)
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Rulon Washington sank a three-pointer with one second left in overtime and Delaware pulled out a 81-78 victory over George Mason Wednesday night. George Mason scored eight straight points to tie the score at 69-69 with 1:13 left in regulation on a three-point play by John Vaughan. Robin Wentt's dunk gave the Hens a 71-69 lead with 51 seconds left, but Tony Skinn fed Jai Lewis for a layup with 37 seconds left to knot the score at 71-71. All five starters for the Blue Hens (6-9, 3-1 Colonial Athletic Association) in double figures. Washington led with 14 points, while Harding Nana posted his seventh straight double-double with 20 points and 12 rebounds. Mike Slattery added 15 points and eight assists, Wentt scored 12 points and pulled 10 rebounds, and Andrew Washington contributed 16 points. Lamar Butler led the Patriots (7-6, 2-2 CAA) with 19 points while Lewis added 16 points and eight rebounds and Skinn added 14 points.
